From: Kreijstal <kreijstal@hotmail.com>
Subject: ui_qt: move QStringList declaration outside extern "C" block

string_split_to_qt() returns QStringList (a C++ template instantiation
of QList<QString>). Declaring it inside the RETRO_BEGIN_DECLS /
RETRO_END_DECLS block makes the prototype `extern "C"`, which is
ill-formed for any function returning a non-POD C++ type and triggers
-Wreturn-type-c-linkage. gcc tolerates the warning, but clang 22 ICEs
during template instantiation in dependent translation units (e.g.
ui/drivers/qt/qt_downloads.cpp).

Move the declaration past RETRO_END_DECLS so it has C++ linkage. The
function is only called from C++ code (the Qt UI), so this is a safe
rearrangement with no ABI change.

--- a/ui/drivers/ui_qt.h
+++ b/ui/drivers/ui_qt.h
@@ -673,9 +673,9 @@ typedef struct ui_window_qt
    MainWindow *qtWindow;
 } ui_window_qt_t;

-QStringList string_split_to_qt(QString str, char delim);
-
 RETRO_END_DECLS

+QStringList string_split_to_qt(QString str, char delim);
+
 #endif
